    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Matthew",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 6,
        "summary": "Jesus continues the Sermon on the Mount\u2014He teaches the disciples the Lord's Prayer\u2014They are commanded to seek first the kingdom of God and His righteousness.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Take heed that ye do not your alms before men, to be seen of them: otherwise ye have no reward of your Father which is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 6:1 And it came to pass that, as Jesus taught his disciples, he said unto them, Take heed \u2026 3\u00a0Ne. 13:1 (1\u201334).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0righteousness, acts of religious devotion. TG\u00a0Almsgiving; Generosity; Motivations; Poor.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore when thou doest thine alms, do not sound a trumpet before thee, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may have glory of men. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0pretenders; the Greek word means \u201ca play actor,\u201d or \u201cone who feigns, represents dramatically, or exaggerates a part.\u201d TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:35 (34\u201335).",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 157
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But when thou doest alms, let not thy left hand know what thy right hand doeth:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That thine alms may be in secret: and thy Father which seeth in secret himself shall reward thee openly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Welfare.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 14:14.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when thou prayest, thou shalt not be as the hypocrites are: for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen of men. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 31:14 (14\u201322).",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But thou, when thou prayest, enter into thy closet, and when thou hast shut thy door, pray to thy Father which is in secret; and thy Father which seeth in secret shall reward thee openly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 33:7 (4\u201311); 34:26 (17\u201327).",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 4:33.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meditation.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 151
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 174
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But when ye pray, use not vain repetitions, as the heathen do: for they think that they shall be heard for their much speaking.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 5:2; Alma 31:20; 3\u00a0Ne. 19:24.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heathen.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not ye therefore like unto them: for your Father knoweth what things ye have need of, before ye ask him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:83 (81\u201386). TG\u00a0God, Intelligence of; God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 23:1.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "After this manner therefore pray ye: Our Father which art in heaven, Hallowed be thy name.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0It is in this way that you ought to pray.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God the Father, Elohim.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0Let Thy name be sanctified.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Name.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done in earth, as it is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, on Earth; Millennium.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Will of.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0on earth.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Give us this day our daily bread.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bread.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0debts, offenses, faults, or sins. TG\u00a0Debt.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil: For thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, for ever. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 6:14 And suffer us not to be led into temptation\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Syriac: do not let us enter into temptation.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temptation; Test.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0but protect us from the evil one. TG\u00a0Deliver; Evil.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 29:11. TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For if ye forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if ye forgive not men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover when ye fast, be not, as the hypocrites, of a sad countenance: for they disfigure their faces, that they may appear unto men to fast. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 7:5 (5\u20136).",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 141
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0receive.",
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 175
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But thou, when thou fastest, anoint thine head, and wash thy face;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That thou appear not unto men to fast, but unto thy Father which is in secret: and thy Father, which seeth in secret, shall reward thee openly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fast, Fasting; Motivations.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lay not up for yourselves treasures upon earth, where moth and rust doth corrupt, and where thieves break through and steal:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Managing Finances in.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0dig through (as an earthen wall).",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p19",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt, and where thieves do not break through nor steal:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 10:34; 1\u00a0Pet. 1:4 (1\u201316). TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stealing.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The light of the body is the eye: if therefore thine eye be single, thy whole body shall be full of light.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 13:22; Morm. 8:15; D&C 4:5; 59:1 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0healthy, sincere, without guile. JST\u00a0Matt. 6:22 \u2026 single to the glory of God \u2026 TG\u00a0Dedication.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 93:28 (28, 36\u201338).",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But if thine eye be evil, thy whole body shall be full of darkness. If therefore the light that is in thee be darkness, how great is that darkness!",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "No man can serve two masters: for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to the one, and despise the other. Ye cannot serve God and mammon.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Loyalty.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Service.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:39 (39\u201342).",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idolatry; Treasure; Worldliness.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 169
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore I say unto you, Take no thought for your life, what ye shall eat, or what ye shall drink; nor yet for your body, what ye shall put on. Is not the life more than meat, and the body than raiment?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 6:25\u201327 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0anxious concern. Ps. 55:22; Prov. 16:3; Luke 12:22; Philip. 4:6; 3\u00a0Ne. 13:25; D&C 84:81. TG\u00a0Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold the fowls of the air: for they sow not, neither do they reap, nor gather into barns; yet your heavenly Father feedeth them. Are ye not much better than they?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Which of you by taking thought can add one cubit unto his stature?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And why take ye thought for raiment? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow; they toil not, neither do they spin:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meditation.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And yet I say unto you, That even Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, if God so clothe the grass of the field, which to day is, and to morrow is cast into the oven, shall he not much more clothe you, O ye of little faith?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore take no thought, saying, What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, Wherewithal shall we be clothed?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1197
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "(For after all these things do the Gentiles seek:) for your heavenly Father knoweth that ye have need of all these things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 8:8; D&C 84:83.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But seek ye first the kingdom of God, and his righteousness; and all these things shall be added unto you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 6:38 Wherefore, seek not the things of this world but seek ye first to build up the kingdom of God, and to establish his righteousness\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 3:13; Alma 39:14 (12\u201314); D&C 6:7 (6\u20137); 11:23; 68:31 (31\u201332); 106:3. TG\u00a0Commitment; Dedication; Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 3:2. TG\u00a0Mission of Early Saints; Objectives.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:21. TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness; Righteousness.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:10. TG\u00a0Blessing.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 5:11 (10\u201313); Mosiah 2:41. TG\u00a0Abundant Life.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Take therefore no thought for the morrow: for the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself. Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:84.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}